text: Day   of posting random pigeon facts According to a nobel prize winning experiment by psychologist Shigeru Watanabe  pigeons were trained to distinguish between the paintings of Monet and Picasso The pigeons were even able to use their knowledge of impressionism and cubism to identify paintings of other artists in those movements  Later  Watanabe taught other pigeons to distinguish watercolor images from pastels And in a   experiment  captive pigeons he d borrowed were shown almost two dozen paintings made by students at a Tokyo elementary school  and were taught which ones were considered  good  and which ones were considered  bad  He then presented them with   new paintings and the avian critics managed to correctly guess which ones had earned bad grades from the school s teacher and a panel of adults  Watanabe s findings indicate that wild pigeons naturally categorize things on the basis of color  texture  and general appearance
